The old saying to handle yourself is strong, as is the feeling of being perceived as a weak person if you talk openly about problems.
Friends is one of the series that comes to mind when I try to offer more mechanisms of psychological adaptation in the long run.
The series highlighted the small moments of friendship between men.
As much as objective, outside intervention helps, through the phone, people reached in moments of despair, long-term support comes from family and close friends.
